CSS - Cascading Style Sheet Language
• is used to give a design, model, layout and resolution of HTML document
• describes how elements should be rendered on screen
• case sensitive
___
𝗖𝗦𝗦 𝗦𝗬𝗡𝗧𝗔𝗫
___
CSS RULESET/RULE or "CSS Syntax" is composed of selector and a declaration block.

• Selector or group of selector -  are the entire elements
• Declaration Block - the main function of elements
• Declaration - these are the value inside the Declaration Block
it has a semicolon at the end of statement

• CSS Declaration is composed of Property Separator and Value
e.g.
___
background-color : lightblue;
___
• background-color - property
• : - separator
• lightblue - value
___
• Property - human readable identifier indicates which stylistic features to change.
• Value - given to a property, specific style should he changed
---
𝗖𝗦𝗦 𝗜𝗡𝗦𝗘𝗥𝗧𝗜𝗡𝗚
___
• there are three ways to insert a CSS into an HTML document.

1. Internal Styling Sheet
2. External Styling Sheet
3. Inline Styling

• Internal Styling Sheet - when a [single] HTML Document has it's unique styles.
• External Styling Sheet - when a [multiple] HTML pages have the same styles.
• Inline Styling - styling a single element, using "style attribute"
